==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: mortar board
<hw>mortar board</hw></mhw> <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A small square board with a handle beneath, for holding
mortar; a hawk; used by masons to hold or carry mortar.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An academic cap topped by broad, projecting, stiff
and flat square top, with a tassel attached to the top and hanging down.
It was once worn by students in some colleges, but is now worn usually
only at graduation ceremonies.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mortgage</ent>⟦br⟧
